me.armar.plugins.autorank.api
Class API

java.lang.Object
  me.armar.plugins.autorank.api.API

public class API
extends java.lang.Object

Autorank's API class:

You, as a developer, can you use this class to get data from players or data about groups. The API is never finished and if you want to see something added, tell us!

Author:
Staartvin

getNextRankupGroup

public java.lang.String getNextRankupGroup(org.bukkit.entity.Player player)
Gets the permission group that the player will be ranked up to after he completes all requirements.

NOTE: This does not mean the player will always be ranked up to this group. If a requirement has its own 'rank change' result, the player will be ranked up to that group and not the 'global results' group.

Parameters:
player - Player to get the next rank up for.
Returns:
The name of the group the player will be ranked to; null when no rank up.

registerRequirement

public void registerRequirement(java.lang.String uniqueName,
                                java.lang.Class<? extends Requirement> clazz)
Register a requirement that can be used in the advanced config. The name should be unique as that is the way Autorank will identify the requirement.

The name will be the name that is used in the config.

Parameters:
uniqueName - Unique name identifier for the requirement
clazz - Requirement class that does all the logic
